<br>
With enough early warning, even something as simple as changing the impactor's reflectivity could be sufficient to avert a collision.<br>
<br>
For example:<br>
<br>
A relatively low-albedo asteroid is determined to be on a direct course to earth..but with a proposed impact timeframe of a century or more away.<br>
<br>
An unmanned craft..as fast as is currently avaliable..is dispatched to intercept..with a payload of enough metallic &quot;paint&quot; to coat most of it's surface..several thousand cubic feet, say...<br>
<br>
